# DR-002 — Microcontroller Selection

**Document ID:** DR-002  
**Status:** Approved  
**Date:** July 19, 2026  
**Author:** Miller Sykes

## Purpose

Select the primary microcontroller platform for Project Aegis.

## Candidates Considered

- STM32
- RP2040
- ESP32

## Evaluation

### STM32
Pros
- Industry standard
- Excellent peripheral set
- Strong development tools
- Widely used in aerospace, robotics, automotive, and industrial systems

Cons
- Steeper learning curve

### RP2040
Pros
- Inexpensive
- Beginner friendly

Cons
- Less representative of professional embedded development

### ESP32
Pros
- Built-in Wi-Fi and Bluetooth
- Large ecosystem

Cons
- Wireless features are unnecessary for early project goals
- Less suitable as a first embedded platform for Project Aegis

## Decision

Project Aegis will use the STM32 family.

The initial development board will be the STM32 Nucleo-64 (STM32G474RE).

This platform best satisfies the project's goals of learning professional embedded systems engineering while providing sufficient performance and peripherals for future expansion.

